All repository modifications must be performed exclusively via:

./llm/ai_edit.sh

Rules:

* Never edit files directly
* Never output inline patches
* Never use direct write tools
* Every mutation must invoke:
  ./ai_edit.sh "<instruction>" <files>

GOOD:
./ai_edit.sh "update parser logic" parser.py

BAD:
./ai_edit.sh "improve parser"

Requirements:

* Always specify target files
* Keep changes atomic
* Re-read repository state after every execution
* Assume git commits are the source of truth

Before any modification, verify:

1. Am I using ./llm/ai_edit.sh?
2. Did I specify files?
3. Is this atomic?

Implement the following workflow

User task
↓
Cline analyzes repo
↓
Cline emits ONE ai_edit.sh command
↓
Aider edits + commits
↓
Cline re-reads repo
↓
Repeat
